Analysis

Charles Marks

January 16, 2019

  • The Analysis Plan
  • First, Upload the DataSet and Split By Site
  • Site-Specific Multivariate Models
    • ECIV
  • MV
    • STAHR
    • VDUS
    • Prediction
  • Three Site MV Model
  • Does Site Moderate Any of the Variables

The Analysis Plan

o First, a site specific multivariate regression will be developed for each North American site: San Diego, Tijuana, and Vancouver.

o Then, a meta-analysis will be conducted, combining data from each North American site to run the multivariate regression on the combined data.

(Charlie insertion) Use results from step one as predictive model in other states.

First, Upload the DataSet and Split By Site

df <- read.csv("final_dataset.csv", header = TRUE)

df <- df[which(!is.na(df$Years_Since_First_Injection)),]
df <- df[which(df$Gender != "Transgender" ),]
df <- df[which(!is.na(df$Ever_Initiated)),]
df <- df[which(!is.na(df$Past_6Mos_Initiated)),]

df$stable_housing <- 0
df$stable_housing[df$Homeless == "No"] <- 1
df$stable_housing <- factor(df$stable_housing, levels = c(0,1), labels = c("No","Yes"))

df$new_initiator <- 0
df$new_initiator[df$Ever_How_Many_Initiates == df$Past_6Mos_How_Many_Initiates & df$Past_6Mos_How_Many_Initiates > 0] <- 1
df$new_initiator <- factor(df$new_initiator, levels = c(0,1), labels = c("No","Yes"))

df$Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos <- 1
df$Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos[df$new_initiator == "Yes" | df$Ever_Initiated == "No"] <- 0
df$Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos <- factor(df$Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos, levels = c(0,1), labels = c("No","Yes"))

df_ECIV <- df[which(df$SITE == "ECIV"),]
df_STAHR <- df[which(df$SITE == "STAHR"),]
df_VDUS <- df[which(df$SITE == "VDUS"),]

Site-Specific Multivariate Models

Bivariate Analyses

Multivariate Log Reg

MV

First we just want to build MV model for never and ever

ECIV.model.null = glm(Past_6Mos_Initiated ~ 1, 
                 data=df_ECIV,
                 family = binomial(link="logit")
                 )

ECIV.model.full = glm(Past_6Mos_Initiated ~ Age + Gender + Years_Since_First_Injection + stable_housing +Past_6Mos_Heroin_NonInjection_Use + Past_6Mos_Heroin_Injection_Use + Past_6Mos_Cocaine_NonInjection_Use + Past_6Mos_Cocaine_Injection_Use + + Past_6Mos_Meth_NonInjection_Use + Past_6Mos_Meth_Injection_Use + Past_6Mos_Injection_Frequency + Past_6Mos_MAT + Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos, 
                 data=df_ECIV,
                 family = binomial(link="logit")
                 )

ECIV.step.results <- step(ECIV.model.null,
     scope = list(upper=ECIV.model.full),
             direction="both",
             test="Chisq",
             data=df_ECIV, trace = 0)

ECIV.final.model <- eval(ECIV.step.results$call)

ECIV.results <- round(exp(cbind(OR = coef(ECIV.final.model), confint(ECIV.final.model))),2)
print("The Results of the Stepwise Model")
## [1] "The Results of the Stepwise Model"

                 data=df_VDUS,

                 )

Prediction

So, we will use the models as a predictive model on the other sites to see if the results from one site are an “effective” tool for understanding initiation in other sites. There will be six total predictions run, corresponding to the three sites predicting the other two sites each.

ECIV as predictor

So we will take our two final ECIV models, ECIV.final.model and ECIV.model.full to predict the outcome in STAHR and VDUS

ECIV.STAHR.pr <- predict(ECIV.final.model, df_STAHR, type="response")
ECIV.STAHR.pred <- ROCR::prediction(ECIV.STAHR.pr, df_STAHR$Past_6Mos_Initiated)
ECIV.STAHR.perf <- ROCR::performance(ECIV.STAHR.pred,measure = "tpr",x.measure = "fpr")
plot(ECIV.STAHR.perf,main="ROC Curve for ECIV Stepwise Model on STAHR",col=2,lwd=2)
abline(a=0,b=1,lwd=2,lty=2,col="gray")

library(jtools)

model <- glm(Past_6Mos_Initiated ~  Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos*SITE, data = df, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
cat_plot(model, pred = Initiated_Ever_Prior_To_Past_6Mos, modx = SITE)

model <- glm(Past_6Mos_Initiated ~  Age*SITE, data = df, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
interact_plot(model, pred = Age, modx = SITE, interval = TRUE, int.type = "confidence", int.width = .8)

model <- glm(Past_6Mos_Initiated ~  Years_Since_First_Injection*SITE, data = df, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
